      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an aging Labrador, a balanced diet is key, and you'll want to look for a high-quality food that supports joint health and muscle mass. Generally, a protein level between 25-35% is good for maintaining lean muscle, while the fat content should be moderate, ideally around 15-20%. However, always check the specific nutritional analysis and consult with your veterinarian for advice tailored to your lab's exact health needs.",
